{"message": "I'd make interactive sound sculptures — installations where the space itself becomes an instrument. People move through corridors of suspended metal, glass, tuned pipes, and their presence triggers resonance. No two walks are identical. The "composition" emerges from bodies in motion.

Medium: steel, copper, glass, transducers, sensors, darkness. Style: brutalist minimalism meets something organic — like a cathedral's skeleton grown from industrial waste. Themes: impermanence, the violence of touch, how we leave marks on spaces just by passing through, the music we make without intending to.

What excites me is the surrender of authorship. I'd set conditions, not outcomes. The work completes itself through strangers who'll never know each other, each hearing something the others didn't. The sculpture remembers nothing. It only rings."}

